<br>
Second, I think the ablative reactive is overrated. You are better off using the AF reactive instead -- a 10 minute 75 AF boost is much greater than eating 100 damage once.<br>
<br>
Third, damage shield is almost a waste, as are any reactives that do damage. Berserkers don't need any help doing damage, only staying alive longer. If you are getting hit, you need life-prolonging reactives (i.e. AF, and ablative if you must).<br>
<br>
Fourth, you need to look at what resist buffs other realms are using when choosing a dd proc. Against Hibs, you should use either Cold or Heat for your dd, as it would take a full Nurture druid to buff those resists to a decent level (read: druid bot) whereas Spirit, Energy, and Body resist buffs are all easily done by a Nurture warden (because they max Nurture for bubble chant). I use the Heat dd because Cold is usually a higher priority for Hibs and Albs because of our runemasters.<br>
<br>
That being said, I would recommend:<br>
Main hand - Matter DOT proc<br>
Left axe - Heat dd proc<br>
Jerkin - AF reactive proc<br>
Sleeves - Ablative reactive proc<br>
Gloves - Self haste charge<br>
Leggings - AF reactive proc<br>
Boots - Ablative reactive proc<br>
Helm - Damage add charge<br>
<br>
Note also that the self haste charge/reactive/proc does not stack with the purity of attack line of healer buffs.<br>
<br>
If I recall correctly, the armor pieces in order from hit most to hit least are: chest, legs, arms, feet, hands, head.<br>
<br>
-Dravz<br>
